data.body:
After the description of JSDoc is incorrect shall bear count of spaces in the transition to a new line.

- VSCode Version:
![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/3082812/20633199/f1b41b3a-b354-11e6-84c0-c5983fab31cb.png)

- OS Version: Linux Mint 18 x64

Steps to Reproduce:

```js
/**
 * @class My
 * @prop {string} name
 */
class My {
   constructor() {
      this.name = 'MyName';
   }

   /**
    * @method func
    * @param {string} p1
    */
   func() {

   }
}
```

1. In the code in the `label 1` press `Enter`;
2. Print `test`;
3. See four spaces in `label 2`;
4. Real spaces is a three (`label 3`).

screen1 | screen 2
---|---
![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/3082812/20633247/74d0e3b8-b355-11e6-8675-bd3cc8ce3de6.png) | ![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/3082812/20633244/6f68e13c-b355-11e6-8c19-fbf53cd59f08.png)

In the description of the JSDoc inside the class declaration is not added symbol `*` when moving to a new line.

- VSCode Version: 
![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/3082812/20632989/e4e0199c-b352-11e6-8de7-b2e8563688a4.png)

- OS Version: Linux Mint 18 x64

Steps to Reproduce:

```js
/**
 * @class My
 * @prop {string} name
 */
class My {
   constructor() {
      this.name = 'MyName';
   }

   /**
    * @method func
    * @param {string} p1
    */
   func() {

   }
}
```
1. In the code in the `label 1` press `Enter`;
2. `*` added in new line (`label 2`);
3. In the code in the `label 3` press `Enter`;
4. `*` not added in new line (`label 4`).

screen1 | screen 2
---|---
![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/3082812/20633042/4c50bf50-b353-11e6-95c8-60a8338d89dd.png) | ![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/3082812/20633016/259914de-b353-11e6-9964-f8c6cf9ac172.png)
